# CI/CD Workflow Conventions

## Workflows

| File | Trigger | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| `build-test-deploy-webapp.yml` | Push/PR to `main`, manual dispatch | `pnpm lint:ci`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`, Playwright e2e; deploy after CI on push to `main` or manual run (`deploy` input) |
| `pr-review.yml` | PR opened/sync | PR description auto-fill, Claude Code review |

## CI requirements

- Node version from `.nvmrc`; pnpm 9; frozen lockfile
- Must pass lint, unit tests, production build, and e2e (Chromium)
- E2E needs `E2E_USERNAME` / `E2E_PASSWORD` secrets in CI

## Rules

- Do not skip CI without team agreement
- New features should include unit tests; auth/navigation changes should consider e2e coverage
